23/07/2006
SOFIA, Bulgaria -- A four-day international drill titled "EU -- Overcoming of Consequences of Terror Acts in Southeast Europe" opened in Bulgaria Sunday (23 July). Rescue teams from Bulgaria, Greece, Hungary, Romania, Slovakia and Slovenia are participating in the drill, which is aimed at improving co-ordination and interoperability of EU and SEE states in dealing with terror threats. (Darik - 23/07/06; Bulgarian Government - 21/07/06)
